sandy back
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:1. a sheep with fine sand and dirt in its wool [after rubbing in dirt or small stones.] 2. the fleece from such a sheep.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:shivey back; seedy back
Pronunciation:
Notes:
